titlestmt.titleproper: Nelson A. Rockefeller gubernatorial records, Office Subject Files, Series 37
A Guide to the Nelson A. Rockefeller gubernatorial records, Office Subject Files, Series 37 FA439

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2015-08-11 01:51:14 -0400.

did.unittitle: Nelson A. Rockefeller gubernatorial records, Office Subject Files, Series 37

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: Microfilm of Series 37 is open for scholarly research. The original paper records cannot be viewed.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation note
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

phystech.head: Physical Characteristics and Technical Requirements note
phystech.p: The original paper records have been reformatted to microfilm.

arrangement.head: Arrangement note
arrangement.p: Subseries 1: First Administration, 1959-1962. Subseries 2: Second Administration, 1963-1966. Subseries 3: Third Administration, 1967-1970. Subseries 4: Fourth Administration, 1971-1973.
Material is arranged alphabetically by subject within each subseries.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Major subjects contained in the files include:

Administration. Aging. Agriculture. Authorities and Commissions. Banking. Civil Defense. Commemorative Observance. Conservation. Consumers. Correction. Disasters. Discrimination. Education. Executive Clemency. Extradition. Fiscal. Fund raising. Government. Health & Sanitation. Honorary Designation. Horse Racing. Housing. Insurance. Investigations. Invitations. Judiciary. Labor. Law. Legislation. Licensing. Mental Hygiene. Military and Naval. Organizations. Parks and Recreation facilities. Personnel Administration. Politics. Property. Public Safety. Public Utilities. Public Works. Regrets. Resignations and Vacancies. Statements. Transportation. Veterans. Welfare. Youth.

processinfo.head: Processing Information note
processinfo.p: This guide was compiled by Brendan Sobie, Rockefeller Archive Center, 1993 and 1994.
